33 following the month in which the covered employee's contribution amounts
34 are withheld from his or her paycheck, the failure to remit such contributions
35 on a timely basis shall be subject to the same sanctions as employer
36 misappropriation of employee wage withholdings and to penalties.
37 "§ 143B-437.126. Rules for the North Carolina Work and Save Program.
38 The Board shall adopt rules to implement the Program that:
39 (1) Establish the processes for enrollment and contributions to Payroll Deduction
40 IRAs under the Program, including elections by covered employees,
41 withholding by covered employers of employee payroll deduction
42 contributions from wages and remittance for deposit to IRAs, and voluntary
43 enrollment and contributions by others, including self-employed individuals
44 and independent contractors, through payroll deduction or otherwise.
45 (2) Establish the processes for withdrawals, rollovers, and direct transfers from
46 IRAs under the Program in the interest of facilitating portability and
47 maximization of benefits.
48 (3) Establish processes for phasing in enrollment of eligible individuals.
49 (4) Conduct outreach to individuals, employers, other stakeholders, and the public
50 regarding the Program. Specify the contents, frequency, timing, and means of
51 required disclosures from the Program to covered employees, participants,
Page 8 DRH40064-MCa-6A

