1 (5) Individuals' awareness of or compliance with the conditions and other
2 provisions of the tax laws that determine which individuals are eligible to
3 make tax-favored contributions to IRAs, in what amount, and in what time
4 frame and manner.
5 (6) Any loss, failure to realize any gain, or any other adverse consequences,
6 including, without limitation, any adverse tax consequences or loss of
7 favorable tax treatment, public assistance, or other benefits, incurred by any
8 person as a result of participating in the Program.
9 (b) No covered employer or other employer shall be, or shall be considered to be, a
10 fiduciary in relation to the Program or Trust or any other arrangement under the Program.
11 "§ 143B-437.128. Protection from liability for the State.
12 The State has no duty or liability to any party for the payment of any retirement savings
13 benefits accrued by any individual under the Program. The State, the Board, each member of the
14 Board, and the Program:
15 (1) Shall have no responsibility for compliance by individuals with the conditions
16 and other provisions of the Internal Revenue Code that determine which
17 individuals are eligible to make tax-favored contributions to IRAs, in what
18 amount, and in what time frame and manner.
19 (2) Shall have no duty, responsibility, or liability to any party for the payment of
20 any benefits under the Program, regardless of whether sufficient funds are
21 available under the Program to pay such benefits.
22 (3) Do not and shall not guarantee any interest rate or other rate of return on or
23 investment performance of any contribution or account balance.
24 (4) Shall have no liability or responsibility for any loss, deficiency, failure to
25 realize any gain, or any other adverse consequences incurred by any person as
26 a result of participating in the Program.
27 "§ 143B-437.129. Confidentiality of participant and account information.
28 Individual account information relating to accounts under the Program and relating to
29 individual participants, including, but not limited to, names, addresses, telephone numbers, email
30 addresses, personal identification information, investments, contributions, and earnings, is
31 confidential, is not a public record as defined in G.S. 132-1, and may not be disclosed except as
32 follows:
33 (1) To the extent necessary to administer the Program in a manner consistent with
34 this Article, the tax laws of this State, and the Internal Revenue Code; or
35 (2) To the extent that the individual who provides the information or is the subject
36 of the information expressly agrees in writing to the disclosure of the
37 information.
38 "§ 143B-437.130. Funding of Program.
39 The North Carolina Small Business Retirement Savings Administrative Fund is established,
40 to be held in trust separate and distinct from the General Fund. Interest earned by the
41 Administrative Fund shall be credited to the Administrative Fund. Moneys in the Administrative
42 Fund are continuously appropriated to the Board. The Administrative Fund consists of:
43 (1) Moneys appropriated to the Administrative Fund by the General Assembly.
44 (2) Moneys transferred to the Administrative Fund from the federal government,
45 other State agencies, or local governments.
46 (3) Moneys from the payment of application, account, administrative, or other
47 fees and the payment of other moneys due the Board.
48 (4) Any gifts, donations, or grants made to the State for deposit in the
49 Administrative Fund.
50 (5) Earnings on moneys in the Administrative Fund.
51 "§ 143B-437.131. Annual report.
